<bibRefCitation id="6B53ADB1FFCEFFEBE7539049FD22FB24" author="Noskiewicz" box="[542,758,1150,1174]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Noskiewicz, J. (1936) Die Palearktischen Colletes - Arten. Wydawnictwo Towarzystwa Naukowego we Lwowie, Lwow, v + 532 pp .. (Prace Naukowe, ser. 2, No. 3)," type="book" year="1936">
Noskiewicz (
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE7FF9049FD3AFB24" box="[690,750,1150,1174]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1936.0">1936</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, based on a single male collected 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE1389049FB79FB24" box="[1141,1197,1150,1174]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1892.0">1892</number>
by Leder in northern 
<collectingCountry id="77D590D0FFCEFFEBE5DA9095FED3FB08" box="[151,263,1186,1210]" name="Mongolia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus id="D0796EE2FFCEFFEBE4019094FEA8FB09" box="[332,380,1187,1211]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">type</typeStatus>
is lost (
<bibRefCitation id="6B53ADB1FFCEFFEBE4929095FD4AFB08" author="Kuhlmann" box="[479,670,1186,1210]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Kuhlmann, M. (2000) Katalog der palaarktischen Arten der Bienengattung Colletes Latr., mit Lectotypenfestlegungen, neuer Synonymie und der Beschreibung von zwei neuen Arten (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Colletinae). Linzer biologische Beitrage, 32 (1), 155 - 193." type="journal article" year="2000">
Kuhlmann 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE72F9095FD4AFB08" box="[610,670,1186,1210]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but the detailed description and the characteristically shaped S 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE0C39095FA48FB08" box="[1422,1436,1186,1210]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="7.0">7</number>
enabled the unambiguous identification of three males collected in 
<collectingCountry id="77D590D0FFCEFFEBE6C690F1FC02FB6C" box="[907,982,1222,1246]" name="Russia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Russia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="77D590D0FFCEFFEBE14390F1FBAFFB6C" box="[1038,1147,1222,1246]" name="Mongolia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
as 
<taxonomicName id="C8C2ABC3FFCEFFEBE1EC90F0FAC2FB6C" box="[1185,1302,1222,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ravulus">
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE1EC90F0FAC2FB6C" box="[1185,1302,1222,1246]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. ravulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. One of the males was collected together with the hitherto unknown female that is described below. Another female was identified from material in the Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F7DD040FFCEFFEBE58A9104FBEFFADC" blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
To facilitate the identification of this little-known species, illustrations of taxonomically relevant morphological features of the male are provided (
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCEFFEBE7729161FD57FADC" box="[575,643,1366,1390]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,303,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, male: a. head, showing the smooth and shiny end of the clypeus; b. finely striate malar area; c. metasomal terga 1 and 2; d. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view); e. genitalia (dorsal view); f. gonostylus (lateral view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278973/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Figs 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE73A9161FD57FADC" box="[631,643,1366,1390]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
a–f) and the female is described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="47D883CBFFCEFFEBE58A914CFECAFA21" box="[199,286,1403,1427]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph id="0F7DD040FFCEFFEBE58A914CFECAFA21" blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" box="[199,286,1403,1427]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE58A914CFECAFA21" bold="true" box="[199,286,1403,1427]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="47D883CBFFCEFFEBE58A91A9FECDF9F4" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0F7DD040FFCEFFEBE58A91A9FEEEFA05" blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" box="[199,314,1438,1463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE58A91A9FEEEFA05" bold="true" box="[199,314,1438,1463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F7DD040FFCEFFEBE58A91F4FECDF9F4" blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
In the female of 
<taxonomicName id="C8C2ABC3FFCEFFEBE4CD91F4FE20FA69" box="[384,500,1475,1499]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ravulus">
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE4CD91F4FE20FA69" box="[384,500,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. ravulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the punctation of T 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE79891F5FD0BFA68" box="[725,735,1474,1498]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1.0">1</number>
is fine and dense (i &lt;d) (
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCEFFEBE6B091F5FB94FA68" box="[1021,1088,1474,1498]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE17F91F5FB94FA68" box="[1074,1088,1474,1498]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
f), a character only shared with 
<taxonomicName id="C8C2ABC3FFCEFFEBE5DA91D0FEF8FA4C" box="[151,300,1510,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perforator">
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE5DA91D0FEF8FA4C" box="[151,300,1510,1534]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. perforator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCEFFEBE47791D1FE5FFA4C" box="[314,395,1510,1534]" captionStart="FIGURE 22. a" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1758,1781]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,194,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[151,1436,193,1737]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 22. a. Colletes patellatus Pérez, female: head; b. metasomal terga 1 and 2; c. C. perforator Smith, female: head; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2; e. C. impunctatus Nylander, female: head; f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278990/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE42391D1FE5FFA4C" box="[366,395,1510,1534]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
d) and 
<taxonomicName id="C8C2ABC3FFCEFFEBE49B91D0FDB1FA4C" box="[470,613,1510,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patellatus">
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE49B91D0FDB1FA4C" box="[470,613,1510,1534]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. patellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCEFFEBE73E91D1FD10FA4C" box="[627,708,1510,1534]" captionStart="FIGURE 22. a" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1758,1781]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,194,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[151,1436,193,1737]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 22. a. Colletes patellatus Pérez, female: head; b. metasomal terga 1 and 2; c. C. perforator Smith, female: head; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2; e. C. impunctatus Nylander, female: head; f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278990/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE7EA91D1FD10FA4C" box="[679,708,1510,1534]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
b) within the 
<taxonomicName id="C8C2ABC3FFCEFFEBE61591D0FC1DFA4C" box="[856,969,1510,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fodiens">
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE61591D0FC1DFA4C" box="[856,969,1510,1534]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. fodiens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. However, the apical tergal hair bands of 
<taxonomicName id="C8C2ABC3FFCEFFEBE479923CFE7EF991" box="[308,426,1547,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ravulus">
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE479923CFE7EF991" box="[308,426,1547,1571]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. ravulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are much broader than in these species (
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCEFFEBE637923DFC6BF990" box="[890,959,1546,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE6FD923DFC6BF990" box="[944,959,1546,1570]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
e), allowing for a reliable identification of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="47D883CBFFCEFFE8E58A9265FA41FF45" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph id="0F7DD040FFCEFFEBE58A9265FE85F9D9" blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" box="[199,337,1618,1643]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE58A9265FE85F9D9" bold="true" box="[199,337,1618,1643]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F7DD040FFCEFFE8E58A9241FA41FF45" blockId="9.[151,1437,1150,2003]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Bl = 10.0–11.0 mm. 
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE4FA9240FE23F93D" bold="true" box="[439,503,1655,1679]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Head</emphasis>
. L = 2.8–2.9 mm; W = 3.6–3.7 mm. Head wider than long (
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCEFFEBE1FF9241FB2CF93C" box="[1202,1272,1654,1678]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE1A49241FB2CF93C" box="[1257,1272,1654,1678]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Integument black except tips of mandible partly dark reddish-brown. Face except clypeus densely covered with long, whitishgrey, erect hairs. Clypeus and supraclypeal area convex in profile. Clypeus finely and densely punctate and without a median depression; surface between punctures shiny (
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCEFFEBE64292D5FC80F948" box="[783,852,1762,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE60892D5FC80F948" box="[837,852,1762,1786]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Supraclypeal area medially impunctate, laterally with a few, small punctures; surface medially shiny, laterally less so and slightly shagreened. Malar area medially about ¼ as long as width of mandible base, finely striate. Antenna black. 
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE69C931CFB9BF8F1" bold="true" box="[977,1103,1835,1859]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc between punctures smooth and shiny; disc sparsely punctate (i = 2.0–3.0d) (
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCEFFEBE1039379FB47F8D4" box="[1102,1171,1870,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE1CE9379FB47F8D4" box="[1155,1171,1870,1894]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
c). Scutellum anteriorly sparsely punctate with more dense punctation apically, surface smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCEFFEBE16A9345FBBFF838" box="[1063,1131,1906,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE1169345FBBFF838" box="[1115,1131,1906,1930]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
c). Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum covered with yellowish-white erect hairs. Basal area of propodeum as illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCEFFEBE467938DFEB8F860" box="[298,364,1978,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCEFFEBE410938DFEB8F860" box="[349,364,1978,2002]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
d. 
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE4CA938DFE06F861" bold="true" box="[391,466,1978,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Wings</emphasis>
. Hyaline; wing venation dark brown. 
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCEFFEBE636938CFC67F861" bold="true" box="[891,947,1979,2003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Legs</emphasis>
. Integument black. Vestiture whitish, scopa white. 
<emphasis id="3DB60C52FFCDFFE8E5AB94AFFEB6FF02" bold="true" box="[230,354,152,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Metasoma</emphasis>
. Integument black except narrow apical margins of T brownish translucent; T 
<number id="B90AC267FFCDFFE8E1B994A0FB2AFF1D" box="[1268,1278,151,175]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1.0">1</number>
to T 
<number id="B90AC267FFCDFFE8E07194A0FA9CFF1D" box="[1340,1352,151,175]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="3.0">3</number>
with a slight oily-bluish shine. T 
<number id="B90AC267FFCDFFE8E4F5948BFE16FF66" box="[440,450,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1.0">1</number>
sparsely covered with short to long, partly appressed white hairs (
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCDFFE8E1EF948BFB31FF66" box="[1186,1253,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCDFFE8E19B948BFB31FF66" box="[1238,1253,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
f); discs of T 
<number id="B90AC267FFCDFFE8E03F948BFA54FF66" box="[1394,1408,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2.0">2</number>
to T 
<number id="B90AC267FFCDFFE8E5E594E8FF61FF45" box="[168,181,223,247]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0">6</number>
without white hairs; apical tergal hair bands broad (
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCDFFE8E7B094E8FC95FF45" box="[765,833,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCDFFE8E67C94E8FC95FF45" box="[817,833,223,247]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
e). Terga densely and finely punctate (i &lt;d) (
<figureCitation id="97F9CCC5FFCDFFE8E07494E8FAA8FF45" box="[1337,1404,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1754,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1733]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Colletes ravulus Noskiewicz, female: a. head; b. clypeus; c. scutum and scutellum; d. propodeum; e. metasoma (dorsal view); f. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278974/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number id="B90AC267FFCDFFE8E02094E8FAA8FF45" box="[1389,1404,223,247]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
f).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
